description:
Umbral is a dark fantasy book following Rascal, a teenage girl in the Thieve's Guild whose world is turned upside down when she conspires with the prince to steal a ceremonial trinket during a solar eclipse. She learns that shadowy creatures from another realm have invaded her own world and are searching for the item she stole, the Oculus, and have already killed and replaced most of the people she knows, including the royal family and her Guildmaster. Rascal is forced to team up with a mysterious old man named Dalone who seems to know more than he is letting on.

Collected Editions

  • Umbral: Out of the Shadows (#1-6)
  • Umbral: The Dark Path (#7-12)
name: Umbral

description:
English translation of the Japanese manga Centaur no Nayami (セントールの悩み).

Being a teenager is never easy, especially for a centaur! Himeno is a sweet, shy girl, who like many teens her age, struggles with the trials and tribulations of attending high school. The difference is she's a centaur - but she's not alone. In fact, all of her classmates are supernatural creatures, sporting either horns, wings, tails, halos, or some other unearthly body appendage. Yet despite their fantastical natures, Himeno and her best friends - the dragon-winged Nozomi, and Kyoko with her spiraled horns - are down-to-earth, fun-loving teenagers who grapple with issues of life and love in a mostly normal daily school setting.
name: A Centaur's Life

description:
English translation of the Japanese manga Heart no Kuni no Alice - Boushiya to Shinya no Ochakai (ハートの国のアリス～帽子屋と深夜のお茶会～).

A new Alice manga series by the author of the New York Times-bestseller Alice in the Country of Hearts. Blood Dupre is the enigmatic leader of the Hatters, Wonderland's mafia. Along with his second-in-command, Elliot March, also known as the March Hare, Blood Dupre schemes from the shadows inside Hatter Mansion, while keeping his enemies at bay. Yet when Alice Lidell enters his life, she gives the dangerous mafia boss a run for his money.
name: Alice in the Country of Hearts: The Mad Hatter's Late Night Tea Party
